/var untrusted @email = <inbox/message.txt>

/guard before untrusted = when [
  @ctx.op.type == "run" => deny "No trust, no shell"
  * => allow
]

/show @claude("Summarize: @email")           << works

/run cmd {curl -d "@email.trim()" api.com}   << blocked

The `untrusted` label survives `.trim()`. 
No bypass possible.